In 55 smol lines of CSS, we've created a set of reasonable document styles that is _just enough_ to produce a responsive, easily readable document given the use of semantic HTML. Thanks to `flexbox`, `viewport units`, and `clamp`, it's flexible for variable document lengths. The newly supported `:is()` deserves the most credit in terms of reducing lines of code.

While lines of code (short or long) certainly doesn't automatically mean "quality", this demo shows that for a simple project you may not need a framework when a little dash of carefully applied CSS will do!

